article.headline: Delaware 67, Drexel 65
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Harding Nana had 21 points and 12 rebounds to lead Delaware to a 67-65 victory over Drexel on Wednesday night in the teams' Colonial Athletic Association opener. Drexel had a chance to tie the game but Bashir Mason missed a layup with 1 second left. Andrew Washington added 15 points for Delaware (3-3), which snapped a two-game losing streak. Danny Hinds had 16 points for Drexel (2-3), which shot 6-for-26 from the field in the second half. Rulon Washington added 10 points, including two 3-pointers, for Delaware and Mike Slattery had eight assists. Phil Goss and Jeremiah King each had 11 points for Drexel.
